    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted based on regulatory precedent that ASTM F1717 compression-bending is the primary and sufficient design verification test for pedicle screw constructs. All three QoIs satisfy pre-established acceptance bounds. The validation package is deemed sufficient to support the intended regulatory use.",
